strategy: Replace the neural network with a random forest ensemble, using bootstrap aggregating (bagging) to reduce variance. Instead of deriving a "social class interaction score," introduce a time-series-like feature by creating a lagged version of the passenger's age group (e.g., age bucket) based on the average survival rate of passengers from the same Pclass and Embarked group. Use permutation importance to identify the most influential features and apply feature pruning to retain only top 10 variables. Employ stratified k-fold cross-validation with a hold-out validation set for final model tuning. This strategy leverages ensemble diversity and interpretable feature interactions without relying on deep learning or complex transformations.
